Overview
========

edgar is a small LISP Interpreter written in C.

Build Dependencies
==================

 - GNU MP http://gmplib.org/

 - C toolchain: C compiler, linker, assembler, libc, etc.
 - diff(1) (only for running tests)

Runtime Dependencies
====================

 - GNU MP http://gmplib.org/

 Building
 ========

 Standard autotools build (`make check` runs the test suite):

 	$ ./configure --prefix=/usr
	$ make
	$ make check
	# make install

Note: if you're building the sources directly out of git, you'll need autoconf
and automake installed. Then, run this command to generate the configure
script:

	$ autoreconf -i
